<br>
The rest?  They don't look like the kind of lineup that sells systems.  Half of those titles had a game on the Dreamcast...<br>
<br>
I'm the one that said the only games that the X-Box has going for it were ports.  I should be clearer.  The only games *I* see as interesting on the X-Box are ports from the PS2.  (And I believe almost all of them are by Konami.  It bears mentioning that Konami failed to come through on a LOT of big promises for the Dreamcast.  They released a few games early in it's life, then packed up it's tents and left.)<br>
<br>
As for DoA... DoA has never been about gameplay.  It's had a couple of cute innovations, but it's always been more about fan service than anything else.  Almost anything out of SNK in the last few years of it's existence easily ownzorz any DoA game on a gameplay perspective. <p>Daeddwin Proudfoot<br>
