<br>
Nintendo always has made the most reliable systems, always has the strongest self made titles... and unlike the N64 (which was probably the best system released up to that time, just lacked games and support from Nintendo), they have big plans for Gamecube.  They will be allowing a lot of companies make their games, so they will carry a lot of the same big titles that PS2 will have.<br>
<br>
This is personal preferance... but I'm a firm supporter of Nintendo's history when it comes to consoles.  Always has been strong.  PS1, although it had NUMEROUS titles (half of which sucked, but added to the library), had a history of being a mechanical nightmare.  I know many a person on their second and third PS1, while most Super Nintendo's still work great.<br>
<br>
And honestly, PS and X-box pride themselves on titles which you can easily get for your PC, which I'm willing to bet is more of a gaming machine than a console is capable of.  Nintendo's best titles are not available on PC.  You get a broader scope of games<br>
<br>
DVD Player... who doesn't have a DVD player already?  And really, is the $100 worth a generic, optionless DVD player.  Take the $100 you saved with GC, save up another $100, and buy a decent DVD player... /nod<br>
<br>
Horsepower...  GC is no lackey here.  Processor by IBM, graphics by ATI... strong, reputable companies working on the guts of that cute lil cube.<br>
<br>
<br>
